President Obama issued a statement praising the Senate's confirmation of James Comey as the next director of the FBI. He commended Comey's leadership and integrity, stating that he has repeatedly demonstrated his commitment to defending America's security and ideals. The President expressed confidence that the FBI will be in good hands under Comey's leadership. However, he also highlighted the need for the Senate to swiftly confirm Todd Jones as the director of the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Explosives (ATF) to ensure the safety of American families. President Obama urged senators to put aside partisan politics and prioritize the protection of the American people.